        <chunk>
          <text>
            The next wave hits harder. The hostile plants have adapted—Florence was right about that too. They're probing our new defensive perimeter, looking for weaknesses: testing Velvet's barriers with corrosive compounds, sending spore clouds to different heights to find gaps in Remedy's coverage, launching underground feints to distract Runner from key positions. But we adapt too.

            Florence calls out —
            "Velvet, reinforce sector three — they're concentrating acid attacks there. Remedy, spore cloud incoming from above, northeast vector. Runner, underground feint at seven o'clock — ignore it. Protect the southwest load-bearer — that's their real target."

            Velvet shifts growth immediately. The barrier thickens just as hostile corrosive vines hit it. They dissolve the outer layer but can't penetrate deeper.

            Remedy releases counter-agents upward. The clouds meet, neutralize, and fall as harmless residue.

            Runner's vines shift underground. Sure enough, hostile roots attack the southwest position moments later, but Runner is ready — severs them before they can destabilize the structure.

            Florence is calling out threats before they fully develop, reading hostile tactics in real time. It's honestly impressive — and still really awkward, because nobody's talking to her except to acknowledge orders.

            Buddy observes in my mind — «They're working well.»

            I correct — "They're surviving well. There's a difference."

            Holloway relays information between defenders, coordinating their responses, but keeps a careful formality when addressing Florence.

            Holloway asks —
            "Florence, Runner reports underground pressure increasing on the eastern flank. Recommendation?"

            Florence replies —
            "Velvet, shift ten percent growth to eastern underground support. Runner, hold current position for thirty seconds while reinforcement arrives, then fall back to secondary position."

            It works. The eastern flank holds — but there's no warmth in the cooperation. Just cold, functional necessity.

            I'm pressed against a pillar in the defended core, Scout beside me, watching everyone work together while maintaining emotional distance. It's effective but uncomfortable.

            ¶

            Another hostile assault—this time a massive root surge from directly below, trying to punch through the center of our defensive perimeter. If it succeeds, it splits our defenses in two.

            Florence asks urgently —
            "Runner, can you intercept?"

            Runner's voice strains — *"Too big. I can slow it but not stop it."*

            Florence issues rapid commands —
            "Velvet, emergency growth directly over Runner's position. Create a secondary floor above the breach point. Remedy, be ready — if they break through, flood the gap with everything you have. Holloway, prepare to evacuate Kira to the western section if this fails."
          </text>
