        <chunk>
          <text>
            Everyone moves instantly—Runner wraps around the hostile root, slowing its ascent. Velvet grows a thick barrier directly above it—if the root breaks through the floor, it will hit a second barrier instead of empty space. Remedy positions near the threatened area, chemical reserves ready.

            Holloway appears beside me.
            Holloway says, "Kira, if I say 'run,' you run west. Scout will guide you."

            Scout bounces in acknowledgment—already positioned to lead me away.

            The hostile root pushes harder and the floor cracks—Runner is struggling and can't hold it much longer.

            Florence asks, "Velvet, status?"

            Velvet says, "Almost… got it… there!"

            The hostile root breaks through the floor and hits Velvet's emergency growth instead of open air—blocked. The root writhes, trying to break through the second barrier too, but Velvet's growth—thick and desperate—holds.

            Florence calls, "Remedy, now!"

            Remedy floods the gap with aggressive chemicals, and the hostile root withers and pulls back underground.

            We held again.

            I let out a breath I didn't know I was holding; Scout bounces in relief.

            I say, "Nice save," to no one in particular.

            Holloway says, "Florence's coordination was sound."
            Not praise—just acknowledgment.

            The attack continues, but the pattern is clear: hostile plants probe, we respond—they escalate, we adapt. It's a stalemate—they can't break through, we can't drive them away, but we're holding position.

            Hours pass as the assault continues in waves; everyone is exhausted.

            Runner surfaces briefly, vines shredded and leaking.
            Runner says, "I need rest—underground fighting is… extensive."

            Florence says, "Take ten minutes. Velvet, can you extend underground coverage temporarily?"

            Velvet says, "Barely—but yes."

            Florence says, "Do it—Runner, recover fast—we need you back."

            Runner coils near the core, trying to heal; they look awful—injuries everywhere, sap loss significant.

            Remedy looks strained.
            Remedy says, "I have maybe three more counter-agent deployments left. After that—I'm empty."

            Florence says, "Conserve for critical threats only—spore clouds that directly threaten Kira. Let everything else through."

            Velvet says, "I can't maintain this density much longer—the corrosive attacks are damaging me faster than I can repair."

            We're holding, but barely.

            Florence hasn't moved from her central coordination position—she's been doing this for hours, reading hostile tactics, predicting attacks, coordinating responses. It requires constant attention, constant analysis.

            A massive bioluminescent flash from the hostile plants—the brightest yet; some kind of signal.

            Holloway asks, "What's that?"

            Florence watches the pattern carefully.
            Florence says, "Either they're calling for reinforcements… or they're pulling back."

            ¶

            We wait in tense silence.
          </text>
